#. <section class="sutta" id="an3.122"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an3.122:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 3"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 3"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.122:0.2"
msgid "12. Āpāyikavagga"
msgstr "12. Bound for Loss"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an3.122:0.3"
msgid "122. Moneyyasutta"
msgstr "122. Sagacity"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an3.122:1.1"
msgid "“Tīṇimāni, bhikkhave, moneyyāni."
msgstr "“Mendicants, there are these three kinds of sagacity."

msgctxt "an3.122:1.2"
msgid "Katamāni tīṇi?"
msgstr "What three?"

msgctxt "an3.122:1.3"
msgid "Kāyamoneyyaṃ, vacīmoneyyaṃ, manomoneyyaṃ."
msgstr "Sagacity of body, speech, and mind."

msgctxt "an3.122:1.4"
msgid "Katamañca, bhikkhave, kāyamoneyyaṃ?"
msgstr "And what is sagacity of body?"

msgctxt "an3.122:1.5"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu pāṇātipātā paṭivirato hoti, adinnādānā paṭivirato "
"hoti, abrahmacariyā paṭivirato hoti."
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant doesn’t kill living creatures, steal, or have sex."

msgctxt "an3.122:1.6"
msgid "Idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, kāyamoneyyaṃ."
msgstr "This is called ‘sagacity of body’."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an3.122:2.1"
msgid "Katamañca, bhikkhave, vacīmoneyyaṃ?"
msgstr "And what is sagacity of speech?"

msgctxt "an3.122:2.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu musāvādā paṭivirato hoti, pisuṇāya vācāya "
"paṭivirato hoti, pharusāya vācāya paṭivirato hoti, samphappalāpā paṭivirato "
"hoti."
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant doesn’t use speech that’s false, divisive, harsh, or "
"nonsensical."

msgctxt "an3.122:2.3"
msgid "Idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, vacīmoneyyaṃ."
msgstr "This is called ‘sagacity of speech’."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an3.122:3.1"
msgid "Katamañca, bhikkhave, manomoneyyaṃ?"
msgstr "And what is sagacity of mind?"

msgctxt "an3.122:3.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu āsavānaṃ khayā anāsavaṃ cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ "
"diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharati."
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant realizes the undefiled freedom of heart and freedom by "
"wisdom in this very life. And they live having realized it with their own "
"insight due to the ending of defilements."

msgctxt "an3.122:3.3"
msgid "Idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, manomoneyyaṃ."
msgstr "This is called ‘sagacity of mind’."

msgctxt "an3.122:3.4"
msgid "Imāni kho, bhikkhave, tīṇi moneyyānīti."
msgstr "These are the three kinds of sagacity."

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "an3.122:4.1"
msgid "Kāyamuniṃ vacīmuniṃ,"
msgstr "A sage in body, a sage in speech,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.122:4.2"
msgid "cetomuniṃ anāsavaṃ;"
msgstr "and an undefiled sage in heart."

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.122:4.3"
msgid "Muniṃ moneyyasampannaṃ,"
msgstr "A sage, blessed with sagacity,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.122:4.4"
msgid "āhu sabbappahāyinan”ti."
msgstr "has given up everything, they say.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an3.122:4.5"
msgid "Dasamaṃ."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an3.122:4.6"
msgid "Āpāyikavaggo dutiyo."
msgstr ""

#. </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "an3.122:5.1"
msgid "Āpāyiko dullabho appameyyaṃ,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.122:5.2"
msgid "Āneñjavipattisampadā;"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.122:5.3"
msgid "Apaṇṇako ca kammanto,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.122:5.4"
msgid "Dve soceyyāni moneyyanti."
msgstr ""
